⏺ Skill(frontend-design:frontend-design)
  ⎿  Successfully loaded skill

⏺ Aesthetic direction: "Editorial precision." Inspired by financial dossiers and
   printed records. The data is the hero — give it dignity through:

  - Typography: Italic display serif (Instrument Serif) for the title and key
  numbers, paired with the modern monospace-adjacent sans (Geist) for UI and
  tabular mono (Geist Mono) for figures. Strong character contrast: literary
  serif vs. utilitarian sans.
  - Palette: Warm off-white paper (#F8F5F0) instead of cold white — easier on
  the eyes for long data-entry sessions. Deep ink primary, warm gray secondary.
  Single warm rust accent (#B8512B) used sparingly: active tab, primary button,
  one decorative hairline.
  - Layout: Strict grid. Hairline borders (no heavy shadows). Numbers prominent,
   tabular, right-aligned. Generous row height. Modal entrance gentle, not
  flashy.
  - Detail: Small "n°" mark and date stamp near the title, a single italic word
  in the page title for character.

  Implementing now. Starting with the backend summary endpoint, then the
  frontend overhaul.

